# Styling

## Hybrid Approach

This project combines three layers:

1. **Tailwind v4 utilities** — layout, spacing, responsive (`className="md:grid-cols-2 h-[300px]"`)
2. **CSS Modules** — section-specific theming (`page.module.css`, `stage.module.css`)
3. **Global component classes** — `@layer components` in `globals.css` (`.section-container`, `.section-header`)

## Combining Classes

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — module class + global Tailwind component class
<div className={`${styles.sectionThree} section-container`}>
```

## When to Use What

| Need | Use |
|------|-----|
| Layout, spacing, responsive | Tailwind utilities in JSX |
| Section theme, complex selectors | CSS Module in `page.module.css` |
| Reusable cross-section classes | `@layer components` in `globals.css` |
| Component-specific styles | Co-located `*.module.css` (e.g. `stage.module.css`) |

## Tailwind v4

- Configured via `@import "tailwindcss"` in `globals.css` and PostCSS plugin.
- No separate `tailwind.config.js` — do not create one.
- Prettier sorts classes via `prettier-plugin-tailwindcss`.

## Theme

CSS variables in `:root` and `@theme inline` in `globals.css`. Dark mode via `prefers-color-scheme`.
